"The <inline-formula><tex-math notation=\"LaTeX\">$h$</tex-math><alternatives><mml:math><mml:mi>h</mml:mi></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href=\"chen-ieq1-2726541.gif\"/></alternatives></inline-formula>-<italic>extra node-connectivity</italic> of a graph <inline-formula><tex-math notation=\"LaTeX\">$G$</tex-math><alternatives><mml:math><mml:mi>G</mml:mi></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href=\"chen-ieq2-2726541.gif\"/></alternatives></inline-formula> is the size of a minimal node-set, whose removal will disconnect <inline-formula><tex-math notation=\"LaTeX\">$G$</tex-math><alternatives><mml:math><mml:mi>G</mml:mi></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href=\"chen-ieq3-2726541.gif\"/></alternatives></inline-formula>, but each remaining component has no fewer <inline-formula><tex-math notation=\"LaTeX\">$h+1$</tex-math><alternatives><mml:math><mml:mrow><mml:mi>h</mml:mi><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href=\"chen-ieq4-2726541.gif\"/></alternatives></inline-formula> nodes. Based on <inline-formula><tex-math notation=\"LaTeX\">$h$</tex-math><alternatives><mml:math><mml:mi>h</mml:mi></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href=\"chen-ieq5-2726541.gif\"/></alternatives></inline-formula>-extra node-connectivity, the <inline-formula><tex-math notation=\"LaTeX\">$h$</tex-math><alternatives><mml:math><mml:mi>h</mml:mi></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href=\"chen-ieq6-2726541.gif\"/></alternatives></inline-formula>-<italic>extra conditional fault-diagnosability</italic> of networks has been proposed for a better, more realistic measure of networks’ fault-tolerability. It is the maximal <inline-formula><tex-math notation=\"LaTeX\">$x$</tex-math><alternatives><mml:math><mml:mi>x</mml:mi></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href=\"chen-ieq7-2726541.gif\"/></alternatives></inline-formula> such that <inline-formula><tex-math notation=\"LaTeX\">$G$</tex-math><alternatives><mml:math><mml:mi>G</mml:mi></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href=\"chen-ieq8-2726541.gif\"/></alternatives></inline-formula> is <inline-formula><tex-math notation=\"LaTeX\">$h$</tex-math><alternatives><mml:math><mml:mi>h</mml:mi></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href=\"chen-ieq9-2726541.gif\"/></alternatives></inline-formula>-extra conditionally <inline-formula><tex-math notation=\"LaTeX\">$x$</tex-math><alternatives><mml:math><mml:mi>x</mml:mi></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href=\"chen-ieq10-2726541.gif\"/></alternatives></inline-formula>-fault-diagnosable. This paper will establish a relationship between the <inline-formula><tex-math notation=\"LaTeX\">$h$</tex-math><alternatives><mml:math><mml:mi>h</mml:mi></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href=\"chen-ieq11-2726541.gif\"/></alternatives></inline-formula>-extra node-connectivity and <inline-formula><tex-math notation=\"LaTeX\">$h$</tex-math><alternatives><mml:math><mml:mi>h</mml:mi></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href=\"chen-ieq12-2726541.gif\"/></alternatives></inline-formula>-extra conditional fault-diagnosability for a regular graph <inline-formula><tex-math notation=\"LaTeX\">$G$</tex-math><alternatives><mml:math><mml:mi>G</mml:mi></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href=\"chen-ieq13-2726541.gif\"/></alternatives></inline-formula>, under the classic PMC diagnostic model. We will apply the newly found relationship to a variety of well-known regular networks, to directly obtain their <inline-formula><tex-math notation=\"LaTeX\">$h$</tex-math><alternatives><mml:math><mml:mi>h</mml:mi></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href=\"chen-ieq14-2726541.gif\"/></alternatives></inline-formula>-extra conditional fault-diagnosability. The significance of the paper's work is that it relates the notions of <inline-formula><tex-math notation=\"LaTeX\">$h$</tex-math><alternatives><mml:math><mml:mi>h</mml:mi></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href=\"chen-ieq15-2726541.gif\"/></alternatives></inline-formula>-extra node-connectivity and <inline-formula><tex-math notation=\"LaTeX\">$h$</tex-math><alternatives><mml:math><mml:mi>h</mml:mi></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href=\"chen-ieq16-2726541.gif\"/></alternatives></inline-formula>-extra conditional fault-diagnosability, so that a regular network's <inline-formula><tex-math notation=\"LaTeX\">$h$</tex-math><alternatives><mml:math><mml:mi>h</mml:mi></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href=\"chen-ieq17-2726541.gif\"/></alternatives></inline-formula>-extra conditional fault-diagnosability may be known once its <inline-formula><tex-math notation=\"LaTeX\">$h$</tex-math><alternatives><mml:math><mml:mi>h</mml:mi></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href=\"chen-ieq18-2726541.gif\"/></alternatives></inline-formula>-extra node-connectivity is known."
